<div class="mw-parser-output"><p class="mw-empty-elt">

</p>
<table class="infobox vcard" style="width:22em"><tbody><tr><th colspan="2" class="fn org" style="text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;background-color: LightBlue">MCA Records</th></tr><tr><td colspan="2" style="text-align:center"><a href="/wiki/File:MCA_Records_logo_(SVG_Type).svg" class="image"><img alt="MCA Records logo (SVG Type).svg" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/39/MCA_Records_logo_%28SVG_Type%29.svg/180px-MCA_Records_logo_%28SVG_Type%29.svg.png" decoding="async" width="180" height="137" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/39/MCA_Records_logo_%28SVG_Type%29.svg/270px-MCA_Records_logo_%28SVG_Type%29.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/39/MCA_Records_logo_%28SVG_Type%29.svg/360px-MCA_Records_logo_%28SVG_Type%29.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="2731" data-file-height="2086" /></a></td></tr><tr><th scope="row">Parent company</th><td><div class="plainlist"><ul><li><a href="/wiki/MCA_Inc." title="MCA Inc.">MCA Inc.</a> <span style="font-size:85%;">(1967–96)</span></li><li>MCA Music Entertainment Group <span style="font-size:85%;">(1989–96)</span></li><li><a href="/wiki/Universal_Music_Group" title="Universal Music Group">Universal Music Group</a> <span style="font-size:85%;">(1996–2003)</span></li></ul></div></td></tr><tr><th scope="row">Founded</th><td>1934 (as Decca Records)<br />1972 (official)</td></tr><tr><th scope="row">Defunct</th><td>2003</td></tr><tr><th scope="row">Distributor(s)</th><td>Self-distributed</td></tr><tr><th scope="row">Genre</th><td class="category">Various</td></tr><tr><th scope="row">Country of origin</th><td><a href="/wiki/United_States" title="United States">United States</a></td></tr></tbody></table>
<p><b>MCA Records</b> was an American <a href="/wiki/Record_label" title="Record label">record label</a> owned by <a href="/wiki/MCA_Inc." title="MCA Inc.">MCA Inc.</a>, which later gave way to the larger MCA Music Entertainment Group (now <a href="/wiki/Universal_Music_Group" title="Universal Music Group">Universal Music Group</a>), which the label was part of until its dissolution in 2003. The label's country division <a href="/wiki/MCA_Nashville" class="mw-redirect" title="MCA Nashville">MCA Nashville</a> is a still an active imprint of <a href="/wiki/Universal_Music_Group_Nashville" title="Universal Music Group Nashville">Universal Music Group Nashville</a>.
</p>
